<html><head><meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" /><link rel="shortcut icon" href="../icons/favicon.ico" /><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="../styles/branding.css" /><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="../styles/branding-en-US.css" /><script type="text/javascript" src="../scripts/branding.js"> </script><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" /><title>Create A Plugin</title><meta name="Language" content="en-us" /><meta name="Microsoft.Help.Id" content="55568427-55ff-4993-98d7-3a9947fc4f32" /><meta name="Description" content="This walkthrough will provide instructions for creating a new GOLDi plugin." /><meta name="Microsoft.Help.ContentType" content="How To" /><meta name="BrandingAware" content="true" /><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="../styles/branding-Website.css" /><script type="text/javascript" src="../scripts/jquery-1.11.0.min.js"></script><script type="text/javascript" src="../scripts/branding-Website.js"></script><script type="text/javascript" src="../scripts/clipboard.min.js"></script></head><body onload="OnLoad('cs')"><input type="hidden" id="userDataCache" class="userDataStyle" /><div class="pageHeader" id="PageHeader">GOLDi Lab Server<form id="SearchForm" method="get" action="#" onsubmit="javascript:TransferToSearchPage(); return false;"><input id="SearchTextBox" type="text" maxlength="200" /><button id="SearchButton" type="submit"></button></form></div><div class="pageBody"><div class="leftNav" id="leftNav"><div id="tocNav"><div class="toclevel0" data-toclevel="0"><a class="tocCollapsed" onclick="javascript: Toggle(this);" href="#!" /><a data-tochassubtree="true" href="../html\c0564785-82de-4e26-9716-cde0e96cc0d2.htm" title="GOLDi Lab Server" tocid="roottoc">GOLDi Lab Server</a></div><div class="toclevel1" data-toclevel="1" data-childrenloaded="true"><a class="tocExpanded" onclick="javascript: Toggle(this);" href="#!" /><a data-tochassubtree="true" href="../html/55568427-55ff-4993-98d7-3a9947fc4f32.htm" title="Step-by-Step Walkthroughs" tocid="b183c615-dbda-4108-9b27-c38d62041666">Step-by-Step Walkthroughs</a></div><div class="toclevel2 current" data-toclevel="2"><a data-tochassubtree="false" href="../html/55568427-55ff-4993-98d7-3a9947fc4f32.htm" title="Create A Plugin" tocid="55568427-55ff-4993-98d7-3a9947fc4f32">Create A Plugin</a></div></div><div id="tocResizableEW" onmousedown="OnMouseDown(event);"></div><div id="TocResize" class="tocResize"><img id="ResizeImageIncrease" src="../icons/TocOpen.gif" onclick="OnIncreaseToc()" alt="Click or drag to resize" title="Click or drag to resize" /><img id="ResizeImageReset" src="../icons/TocClose.gif" style="display:none" onclick="OnResetToc()" alt="Click or drag to resize" title="Click or drag to resize" /></div></div><div class="topicContent" id="TopicContent"><table class="titleTable"><tr><td class="logoColumn"><img width="50" src="../icons/Help.png" /></td><td class="titleColumn"><h1>Create A Plugin</h1></td></tr></table><span class="introStyle"></span> <div class="introduction"><p>This walkthrough will provide instructions for creating a new GOLDi plugin.</p></div><h3 class="procedureSubHeading">Setting Up the Project</h3><div class="subSection"><ol><li><p>Create a new class library project inside the GOLDi solution.</p><p>
              During the project creation, select a matching solution folder to put the project in, 
              e.g. if the plugin adds the connection to new device types, select the "Physical Links" folder.
            </p><p>
              During creation, select the same .NET Framework version as the GOLDi Server uses. 
              Currently, this is 4.7.1.
            </p></li><li><p>Create a project configuration for the solution configurations.</p><p>
              Currently, only the AnyCPU and x86 platforms are supported. 
              For each of the platforms, the Debug, Release and Stable Build mode have to be configured.
            </p></li><li><p>Set the assembly file name to "Plugin.MyPluginName", where MyPluginName is the name of the plugin.</p><p>
              The name pattern is essential for the automatic discovery of the plugins.
            </p></li><li><p>Set output directory to a folder inside the "Plugins" folder in the GOLDi Servers output directory.</p><p>
              This procedure has to be repeated for all configurations and platforms. 
              Alternatively, you might also copy the PropertyGroups from another already existing plugin project file.
            </p></li><li><p>
              Create references to the GOLDi libraries and prevent Visual Studio from copying them to the project output directory.
            </p><p>
              Usually, referencing the GOLDiCore, GOLDiFabric and GOLDiConcepts library is required. 
              When access to additional classes from the GOLDiServer is needed, consider a refactoring 
              that results in a clean, well-documented interface residing inside the GOLDiConcepts library.
              Follow the patterns used by the interfaces that are already provided by thwe GOLDiConcepts library.
            </p><p>
              To eliminate unnecessary copies of the same assembly, set the "Local Copy" property of the reference to the other
              GOLDi projects to "False". This option can be found in the properties page when selecting the assembly inside the 
              projects references in the solution explorer.
            </p></li></ol></div></div></div><div id="pageFooter" class="pageFooter" /></body></html>